data.title: Weekly Preview May 1: RG Gdynia Rhythmic Stars; European Cup; Portimão International Tournament • USA Gymnastics
data.meta_description: U.S. rhythmic gymnasts will take over Europe this week as they head to several international competitions.
data.text:
U.S. rhythmic gymnasts will take over Europe this week as they head to several international competitions.

RG Gdynia Rhythmic Stars

Rin Keys (Porter Ranch, Calif./Burlo Gymnastics) will be joined by Sarah Mariotti (San Diego, Calif./Pacific Stars Rhythmic Academy) and Pacific Rim Championships junior medalists Isabella Chong (Mission Viejo, Calif./Burlo Gymnastics), Dawn Kim (San Diego, Calif./Pacific Stars Rhythmic Academy) and Natalia de la Rosa (Woodland Hills, Calif./Burlo Gymnastics) at the 2024 Gdynia Rhythmic Stars tournament May 3-5 in Gdynia, Poland.

Competition will kick off Friday, May 3 with junior hoop and ball qualifications at 7:45 a.m. ET, followed by seniors at 11:40 a.m. ET. Clubs and ribbon qualifications start Saturday’s slate with juniors at 8:15 a.m. ET and seniors at 12:10 p.m. ET. Finals are set for Sunday, May 5 beginning at 4:45 a.m. ET. More information can be found on the event’s website.

European Cup

Alexandria Kautzman (Simi Valley, Calif./California Rhythms) will represent the U.S. at the 2024 European Cup May 3-5 in Baku, Azerbaijan.

Individual qualifications will take place on Friday, May 3 beginning at 1 a.m. ET followed by an all-around cross battle on Saturday at 4 a.m. ET. The top 16 athletes will qualify to the all-around cross battle where eight athletes will go head-to-head on ball and eight on hoop to advance to the quarterfinal. The winners will then switch apparatus and compete for a spot in the all-around final. Finalists will perform on ribbon for a medal. All apparatus awards will be determined on Sunday beginning at 2:05 a.m. ET.

Visit the competition website for more information on the European Cup.

Portimão International Tournament

Seniors Jaelyn Chin (Aventura, Fla./Bessonova’s school), Lauren Kramer (San Diego, Calif./Pacific Stars Rhythmic Academy) and Yana Golovan (Las Vegas, Nev./Nevada Rhythmic Academy) and juniors Anastasia Dubinkina (Staten Island, N.Y./Isadora by Matchpoint), Aleksia Khilkevich (Staten Island, N.Y./Isadora by Matchpoint) and Aurora Sullivan (Los Angeles, Calif./Burlo Gymnastics) will be in Portugal from May 4-6 for the 31st Portimão International Tournament.
